<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 7:44AM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...A BAND OF HEAVY SNOW ACROSS RHODE ISLAND AND SOUTHEAST
MASSACHUSETTS...
At 739 AM EST, radar indicated a roughly 20 mile wide band of heavy
snow along a line extending from Quincy to near Providence. This
band has been producing snowfall at the rate of over 2 inches per
hour along with very low visibilities. This band will be slowly
drifting southeast through mid morning.
Locations impacted include...
Providence, New Bedford, Brockton, Quincy, Fall River, Warwick,
Cranston, Pawtucket, Plymouth, Taunton, Weymouth, East Providence,
Braintree, Coventry, Dartmouth, Cumberland, Randolph, North
Providence, South Kingstown and West Warwick.
Due to the rapid accumulation of snow, hazardous driving conditions
will occur. Consider delaying travel if you will be going through
this band of heavy snow.</description>
